Related: gui, UI

Microsoft.com/technet/scriptcenter/topics/htas/tutorial1.mspx >>HTML Applications (HTAs) provide a way for you to wrap your scripts up in a graphical user interface, an interface replete with check boxes, radio buttons, drop-down lists and all those other Windows elements you've grown to love. In this article, the first of a multi-part series, we'll introduce the basics behind creating your very own HTA.
